description.text: gemini-2.0-flash-lite is a multimodal AI model from Google's Gemini family, designed for advanced language understanding and generation tasks.

architecture.text: Transformer-based architecture with advanced attention mechanisms and multimodal capabilities. The Gemini models use a unified architecture that can process text, images, audio, and video inputs seamlessly.

input_modalities.text: Supported input types: text, audio, image. The model can process these data types simultaneously for multimodal understanding.

output_modalities.text: Text generation with support for structured outputs, code generation, and conversational responses.

license_type.text: Google API Terms of Service apply. Commercial usage permitted with appropriate API subscription.

channels.text: Available through Vertex AI (Google Cloud Platform), AI Studio (web interface), and Google Cloud API endpoints. SDK support for Python, Node.js, Go, and Java.

intended_use.text: Designed for text generation, creative writing, code assistance, multimodal understanding, translation, summarisation, and conversational AI applications. Suitable for both research and commercial deployments.

restrictions.text: Usage must comply with Google's AI Principles and Prohibited Use Policy. Not to be used for illegal activities, harassment, deception, or generating harmful content.
